														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1309373">
									

<p>I respect Clef for his opinion, in fact I applaud him for making it. One of the greatest dangers is falling into routine and using references to past hilarity in the place of actually being clever may seem like social bonding, but its really more like some sort of slow, ugly de-evolution where society regresses into something akin to a flock of honking geese telling Chuck Norris jokes and putting Flying Spaghetti Monster decals on their bumpers while wearing Guy Fawkes masks and posting memes on 4chan with iPhones purchased by their parents before doing an essay on it at Know Your Meme.</p>
<p><em>Let's not be those guys.</em></p>
<p>But with God as my witness, <strong>bees will always be funny.</strong></p>
